OL,3,CMan found guilty of murdering 15-year-
OL,4,Cold schoolgirl Elianne Andam
OL,6,FSentamu, who admitted manslaughter,
OL,7,Fclaimed his autism affected his
OL,8,Fability to exercise self control and
OL,9,Fwas therefore not guilty of murder.
OL,11,FHowever, the prosecution rejected the
OL,12,Fassertion saying neither his autism
OL,13,Fnor his troubled background provided
OL,14,Fan excuse for murder.
OL,16,FThe trial heard Sentamu had a long
OL,17,Fhistory of volatile and violent
OL,18,Fbehaviour, having been cautioned for
OL,19,Ftaking a knife to school, and, while
OL,20,Fawaiting trial for Elianne's murder,
OL,21,Fthreatened to "do it again".
